11 interventions, meaning different start dates for the expanded use of family detention. These

12 pseudo-interventions address the possibility that policy changes need time to take effect. The

13 pseudo-interventions analyzed include the months shortly after the conversion of the Karnes

14 County Residential Center, the month of the opening of the South Texas Family Residential

15 Center, and the three months after the opening of the South Texas Family Residential Center.7

16 These models produce qualitatively similar results, wherein the expanded use of family detention

17 is not statistically significantly related to decreases in the monthly number of U.S. Border Patrol

18 apprehensions of family units at the Southwest border.

