Conclusion

17

22. Altogether, data on the monthly number of U.S. Border Patrol apprehensions of

18

family units at the Southwest border shows that recent policies intended to deter families from

19

attempting to enter the U.S. without authorization have not had their desired deterrent effects.

20 • As the data show, the expanded use of family detention is not statistically

21

significantly related to decreases in the monthly number of U.S. Border Patrol

22

apprehensions of family units at the Southwest border. This result is robust when

